-- Singapore’s Olam Plans $500 Mln Russian Venture, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-01-30T05:12:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/singapore-s-olam-plans-500-mln-russian-venture-vedomosti-says.html
Olam International Ltd. (OLAM) , a
Singapore-based agricultural trader may invest $500 million in a
Russian dairy project with local partner Rusmoloko, Vedomosti
newspaper reported, citing an unidentified person close to
 Russia ’s  Agriculture Ministry .  The venture may invest the money in the Penza region of
central Russia over three to five years, the Moscow-based
newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 